$AEHR there is a lot of skepticism here and obviously they do need to secure and announce the orders, but given the hyperscaler guides to date - GOOG specifically with the TPU, but also AMZN ASICs - the below comment last Q by the CEO is particularly relevant.  

&quot;What we get is visibility of a specific GPU or CPU or network processor or an ASIC. And then we hear these things from the customer and then we look externally and what are they telling the Street and try and correlate to those lookups. And I’d say pretty consistently, we hear bigger numbers from the customer than the Street.&quot; 

AEHR knows more than all of us/the street because they are in fact talking to GOOG and the rest. I do not think they deserve the amount of skepticism they are getting

$AEHR some crazy quotes:  

&quot;For some of these big guys at wafer level burden is, you know, 20, 30 systems or so. And these are 4 or $5 million machines. So you get a feel for the size of what that looks like&quot; 

 &quot;When customers ask you things like how many can you make? You get a hint, right? So can the AI business be measured in hundreds of millions of dollars for AEHR, you know, a few years out? Yes&quot; 

 So maybe getting a $50M+ order in the next few months that gets them the 60-80m in bookings. There are some customers worried they would buy out AEHR&#39;s entire capacity. Possibly hundreds of millions of dollars in AI revenue within a few years.  

If the 4.8m shares shorts this have a thesis that AEHR will not penetrate the AI market then they are being proven wrong

